#                                                     graphics protocol)
#   golang.org/x/image/webp                         (WebP image decoding)
#
# `reader` is a one-shot CLI: pass a URL (or file path, or `-` for stdin),
# and it fetches the page, runs Mozilla-Readability-style content
# extraction (via the sibling `journalist/crawler` library) to strip
# navigation/ads/sidebars/social-widgets, converts the cleaned HTML to
# Markdown via JohannesKaufmann/html-to-markdown, embeds inline images
# via Kitty/Sixel/ANSI protocols (selected via --image-mode), and renders
# the final Markdown through glamour's TermRenderer to produce a
# beautifully styled terminal article suitable for `less -R` paging.
# `--eml` switches the input mode to RFC 5322 email parsing (via
# emersion/go-message) so the same readability + Markdown rendering
# pipeline can be applied to email bodies.  `--raw` short-circuits the
# rendering pipeline and emits raw text; `--markdown-output` emits raw
# markdown without the glamour ANSI styling.
#
# === AXIS 183 CONTINUES — terminal markdown rendering libraries ==========
# Axis position: Go=238 continues Axis 183 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# terminal markdown renderer is `github.com/charmbracelet/glamour` by
# Charmbracelet — pure-Go markdown renderer wrapping `goldmark` as the
# parser and adding a `TermRenderer` that emits ANSI-styled output with
# skinnable themes (dracula / dark / light / pink / notty / ascii), word-
# wrap, code-block syntax highlighting via chroma, and table / blockquote
# / heading style overrides.  THE Go answer to "render this markdown
# source as a beautifully formatted terminal block."  Used by gh-cli
# (GitHub CLI's PR/issue body rendering), glow itself (the standalone
# CLI wrapper around glamour), lazygit's commit-message viewer, and
# every Charmbracelet-ecosystem tool that needs in-terminal markdown.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=238     _ggsql               ← previous round (axis 183 OPENS, 1/0/0)
#   Go=238       ← THIS FILE          (axis 183 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=238  ← next round         (axis 183 CLOSES at triple-238, 1/1/1)
#
# Cross-language design notes for axis 183:
#   Rust    : termimad wraps minimad (the parser) + adds an ANSI renderer
#             with skinnable styles + interactive scrolling/paging.  Tied
#             closely to crossterm for cursor / color / size detection.
#             Used by broot/bacon/dysk and the wider Canop ecosystem.
#   Go      : glamour wraps goldmark (the parser) + adds a TermRenderer
#             that emits ANSI escapes + chroma-backed code-block syntax
#             highlighting + skinnable themes.  Tied closely to lipgloss
#             for styling primitives.  Used by gh-cli/glow/lazygit and
#             the wider Charmbracelet ecosystem.
#   JS/Node : marked-terminal wraps marked (the parser) + emits ANSI
#             via chalk for color + cli-table3 for table layout.  Used
#             by hundreds of npm-ecosystem CLI tools.  [TBD next round]
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_reader() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '(-o --markdown-output)'{-o,--markdown-output}'[disable pretty output, output raw markdown instead (skips glamour rendering)]' \
        '(-r --no-readability)'{-r,--no-readability}'[disable making the HTML content readable (skip Mozilla-Readability extraction; emit raw fetched HTML)]' \
        '--no-cycletls[disable use of CycleTLS (the bot-detection-evading TLS fingerprint spoofer)]' \
        '--eml[input is EML (email) format — parse as RFC 5322 MIME via emersion/go-message instead of fetching a URL]' \
        '--raw[output raw text (bypass both readability and Markdown rendering)]' \
        '(-v --verbose)'{-v,--verbose}'[verbose output (use zap.NewDevelopment() logger instead of zap.NewProduction())]' \
        '(-i --image-mode)'{-i,--image-mode}'=[image rendering protocol for inline images (default: ansi)]:mode:(none ansi ansi-dither kitty sixel)' \
        '(-w --terminal-width)'{-w,--terminal-width}'=[explicit terminal width in columns (0 = auto-detect via ioctl TIOCGWINSZ, fallback 80)]:width:' \
        '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[help for reader]' \
        '*:URL or file path or - for stdin:_alternative "urls:URL:_urls" "files:file or - for stdin:_files"'
}

_reader "$@"
